cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

The paper discusses deep neural networks (DNNs) and their performance in machine learning and natural language processing tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also analyzes the outputs of DNNs, which suggests a possible fit with cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper investigates how training size and noise affect DNNs, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper mentions image classification tasks, which could relate to cs.CV (Computer Vision).
